s[264] = "SqlitePassDbo.TSqlitePassDatabase.AttachDatabase^SqlitePassDbo.TSqlitePassDatabase.html#AttachDatabase^Enables to attach one or several foreign <a class=\"normal\"  href=\"SqlitePassDbo.TSqlitePassDatabase.html#Databases\">databases</a> to the current one.^ The attached <a class=\"normal\"  href=\"SqlitePassDbo.TSqlitePassDatabase.html#Databases\">databases</a> must be compatible with the current one (the <a class=\"normal\"  href=\"SqlitePassDbo.TSqlitePassDatabase.html#Databases\">databases</a> must have been created with the same <a class=\"normal\"  href=\"SqlitePassDbo.TSqlitePassDatabase.html#Database\">database</a> manager application). Once a <a class=\"normal\"  href=\"SqlitePassDbo.TSqlitePassDatabase.html#Database\">database</a> is attached, its content becomes available as part of the current <a class=\"normal\"  href=\"SqlitePassDbo.TSqlitePassDatabase.html#Database\">database</a>. Then you can access to tables, queries... as if they were part of the main <a class=\"normal\"  href=\"SqlitePassDbo.TSqlitePassDatabase.html#Database\">database</a>. Usage : <code>AttachDatabase</code>(DatabasePath: String);    ^0"
s[265] = "SqlitePassDbo.TSqlitePassDatabase.Compact^SqlitePassDbo.TSqlitePassDatabase.html#Compact^Compacts the <a class=\"normal\"  href=\"SqlitePassDbo.TSqlitePassDatabase.html#Database\">database</a> content and free unused space^    ^0"
s[266] = "SqlitePassDbo.TSqlitePassDatabase.CreateAggFunction^SqlitePassDbo.TSqlitePassDatabase.html#CreateAggFunction^CreateAggFunc References a new Aggregate User Defined function in the Sqlite <a class=\"normal\"  href=\"SqlitePassDbo.TSqlitePassDatabase.html#Engine\">Engine</a> API As an Example, you can use an SumOdd function to get the Sum of Odd Values : <br> 1 - Reference the SumOdd function in Sqlite <a class=\"normal\"  href=\"SqlitePassDbo.TSqlitePassDatabase.html#Engine\">Engine</a> Unit...^ var SumOddResult: Integer;    <p>procedure TMainForm.Button1Click(Sender: TObject); begin SumOddResult := 0; db.CreateAggFunction('SumOdd', 1, @SumOddStep, @SumOddFinal, @SumOddResult); end; <br> 2 - Execute a query that uses the SumOdd function for instance &quot; Select SumOdd(IntegerField) From IntegerTable;&quot; @be 3 - The SumOdd Function is called every time SQLite processes a row returned by the query <br> 4 - Now, the Query returns the sum of odd Values... <br> Note : The function must be declared 'cdecl'. Please, have a look at SQLite online help for further information on UDF Functions. <br> <br> Procedure SumOdd implementation : <br> procedure SumOddStep(Context: Pointer; nArgs: Integer; Args: <a class=\"normal\"  href=\"SqlitePassUtils.html#PPSqliteValue\">ppSqliteValue</a>); cdecl; var TempRes, Res:integer; begin // We get the initial value of the current row returned by the query TempRes := StrToIntDef(<a class=\"normal\"  href=\"SqlitePassApi_v3.html#SqliteDbv3_value_text\">SqlitePassApi_v3.SqliteDbv3_value_text</a>(Args&circ;),0); // We do something with TempRes if (TempRes mod 2) &gt; 0 then SumOddResult := SumOddResult + TempRes; end;    <p>procedure SumOddFinal(Context: Pointer); cdecl; begin // Send back the final result to SQLite <a class=\"normal\"  href=\"SqlitePassDbo.TSqlitePassDatabase.html#Engine\">Engine</a> <a class=\"normal\"  href=\"SqlitePassApi_v3.html#SqliteDbv3_result_int\">SqlitePassApi_v3.SqliteDbv3_result_int</a>(Context,SumOddResult); // Reset the value for another query SumOddResult := 0; end;    ^0"
s[267] = "SqlitePassDbo.TSqlitePassDatabase.CreateDatabase^SqlitePassDbo.TSqlitePassDatabase.html#CreateDatabase^Creates a new <a class=\"normal\"  href=\"SqlitePassDbo.TSqlitePassDatabase.html#Database\">database</a>^    ^0"
s[268] = "SqlitePassDbo.TSqlitePassDatabase.CreateFunction^SqlitePassDbo.TSqlitePassDatabase.html#CreateFunction^CreateFunc References a new scalar User Defined function in the Sqlite <a class=\"normal\"  href=\"SqlitePassDbo.TSqlitePassDatabase.html#Engine\">Engine</a> API As an Example, you can use an IsOdd function to filter the records returned by a query : <br> 1 - Reference the IsOdd function in Sqlite <a class=\"normal\"  href=\"SqlitePassDbo.TSqlitePassDatabase.html#Engine\">Engine</a> procedure TMainForm.Button1Click(Sender: TObject); begin db.CreateFunction('IsOdd',1,@IsOdd, nil); end; <br> 2 - Execute a query that uses the IsOdd function for instance &quot; Select IntegerField from &quot;IntegerTable&quot; where IsOdd(IntegerField)&gt;0;&quot; @be 3 - The IsOdd Function is called every time SQLite processes a row returned by the query <br> 4 - Now, the Query returns Only Odd Values...^ <br> Note : The function must be declared 'cdecl'. Please, have a look at SQLite online help for further information on UDF Functions. <br> <br> Procedure IsOdd implementation (From SqliteToolBox) : <br> procedure IsOdd(Context: Pointer; nArgs: Integer; Args: <a class=\"normal\"  href=\"SqlitePassUtils.html#PPSqliteValue\">ppSqliteValue</a>); cdecl; var TempRes, Res:integer; begin // We get the initial value of the current row returned by the query TempRes := StrToIntDef(<a class=\"normal\"  href=\"SqlitePassApi_v3.html#SqliteDbv3_value_text\">SqlitePassApi_v3.SqliteDbv3_value_text</a>(Args&circ;),0); // We do something with TempRes if (TempRes mod 2) &gt; 0 then Res := TempRes else Res := 0; // We send back the changed value to Sqlite <a class=\"normal\"  href=\"SqlitePassApi_v3.html#SqliteDbv3_result_int\">SqlitePassApi_v3.SqliteDbv3_result_int</a>(Context,Res); end;    ^0"
s[269] = "SqlitePassDbo.TSqlitePassDatabase.DeleteDatabase^SqlitePassDbo.TSqlitePassDatabase.html#DeleteDatabase^Deletes a <a class=\"normal\"  href=\"SqlitePassDbo.TSqlitePassDatabase.html#Database\">database</a> file.^ Use with caution...    ^0"
